@startuml fig-ethernet-frame
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 10
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12
left to right direction

title Ethernet II Frame Format (IEEE 802.3)

rectangle "Preamble\n7 bytes\n10101010..." as pre #ECEFF1
rectangle "SFD\n1 byte\n10101011" as sfd #ECEFF1
rectangle "Dest MAC\n6 bytes" as dmac #BBDEFB
rectangle "Src MAC\n6 bytes" as smac #BBDEFB
rectangle "EtherType\n2 bytes" as etype #E1BEE7
rectangle "Payload\n46–1500\nbytes" as pay #FFF9C4
rectangle "FCS (CRC-32)\n4 bytes" as fcs #C8E6C9

pre -right-> sfd
sfd -right-> dmac
dmac -right-> smac
smac -right-> etype
etype -right-> pay
pay -right-> fcs

legend bottom
  Preamble and SFD synchronise the receiver clock.
  EtherType identifies the upper-layer protocol
  (0x0800 = IPv4, 0x0806 = ARP, 0x86DD = IPv6).
  Minimum frame size: 64 bytes (excluding preamble).
  FCS detects bit errors via CRC-32.
endlegend
@enduml
